            "title": "G\u00eanero e educa\u00e7\u00e3o : a forma\u00e7\u00e3o educacional para a igualdade de G\u00eanero no Movimento dos Trabalhadores Rurais sem Terra",
            "abstract": [
                "Al\u00e9m de ocupar, resistir e produzir, as mulheres do MST v\u00eam travando uma dura \u201cluta dentro da luta\u201d para superar o machismo e promover a igualdade de g\u00eanero. A educa\u00e7\u00e3o de g\u00eanero nas escolas do movimento, combinada com lutas travadas especialmente pelas mulheres nas assembleias, nas cooperativas e associa\u00e7\u00f5es, nos assentamentos, al\u00e9m da participa\u00e7\u00e3o igualit\u00e1ria nas decis\u00f5es estrat\u00e9gicas do movimento t\u00eam contribu\u00eddo a constru\u00e7\u00e3o de novas rela\u00e7\u00f5es sociais e de g\u00eanero. O patriarcalismo \u00e9 anterior ao modo de produ\u00e7\u00e3o capitalista, mas certamente o capitalismo aprofundou as diferen\u00e7as entre homens e mulheres, entre povos e etnias, e j\u00e1 est\u00e1 cientificamente provado que \u00e9 imposs\u00edvel alcan\u00e7ar a igualdade substantiva entre seres humanos dentro dos marcos deste modo de produ\u00e7\u00e3o b\u00e1rbaro e mesquinho. As mulheres de todas as partes da Am\u00e9rica Latina est\u00e3o travando uma luta ferrenha contra todas as formas de opress\u00e3o que \u2013 quem sabe \u2013 poder\u00e3o desembocar numa sociedade para al\u00e9m do capital. Jeniffer Pess\u00f4a \u2013 nesta pesquisa cuidadosa - traz uma contribui\u00e7\u00e3o fundamental a este debate ao abordar as tem\u00e1ticas de g\u00eanero, do machismo e da educa\u00e7\u00e3o do MST.  HENRIQUE TAHAN NOVAES | UNESP Mar\u00edlia",
                "In addition to occupying, resisting and producing, MST women have been waging a tough \u201cfight within the fight\u201d to overcome sexism and promote gender equality. Gender education in the movement's schools, combined with struggles fought especially by women in assemblies, cooperatives and associations, in settlements, in addition to equal participation in the movement's strategic decisions have contributed to the construction of new social and gender relations. Patriarchy predates the capitalist mode of production, but capitalism has certainly deepened the differences between men and women, between peoples and ethnicities, and it has already been scientifically proven that it is impossible to achieve substantive equality between human beings within the framework of this barbaric mode of production. and petty. Women from all parts of Latin America are waging a fierce struggle against all forms of oppression that \u2013 who knows \u2013 could lead to a society beyond capital. Jeniffer Pess\u00f4a \u2013 in this careful research \u2013 makes a fundamental contribution to this debate by addressing the issues of gender, machismo and education in the MST.  HENRIQUE TAHAN NOVAES | UNESP Mar\u00edlia"
            ],
